definition: to submit (a report etc)/to refer (a problem) to sb
to carry (hanging down from the hand)/to lift/to put forward/to mention/to raise (an issue)/upwards character stroke/lifting brush stroke (in painting)/scoop for measuring liquid
to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]

sentences.english: Material evidence must also be original.
How do I submit an expense report?
For biological products, samples from several consecutively manufactured batches should be submitted.
sentences.chinese: 对于生物制品，应当要提交连续几个生产批次的样品。

sentences.english: Candidates may be required to produce medical proof of their disability.
sentences.chinese: 申请人或须提交医生证明书，以证明他为残疾人士。

sentences.english: The results of the BCA consumer research project also will be presented.
sentences.chinese: 结果基本能力评估的消费者研究项目也将提交。

sentences.english: Indicate by a check mark whether the registrant has filed all reports required.
sentences.chinese: 用对钩标记登记者是否提交了所需报告。

sentences.english: The bill, which has 31 co-sponsors, has been forwarded to the House Ways and Means Committee for consideration.
sentences.chinese: 这项法案已提交众议院筹款委员会审议。

sentences.english: The proxy service monitors the status of each job that has been submitted.
sentences.chinese: 代理服务监视已提交的每个作业的状态。

sentences.english: The editor contains a button that will perform the submission.
sentences.chinese: 该编辑器包含一个将执行提交的按钮。

sentences.english: Two copies of each entry should be submitted.
sentences.chinese: 每件参赛作品需提交两套作品予主办机构。

sentences.english: Enter the data in the form and start the business process by submitting the form.
sentences.chinese: 在表单中输入数据，然后通过提交表单启动业务流程。

sentences.english: Of these assignments, at least one must be revised and resubmitted.
sentences.chinese: 这些报告至少有一篇必须修改后再提交。

sentences.english: The stub and skeleton objects also take care of beginning and committing container-managed transactions.
sentences.chinese: 存根和骨架对象还负责开始和提交容器管理的事务。

sentences.english: Enter the contact's name and then select submit.
sentences.chinese: 进入连络人的姓名，然后选择提交。

sentences.english: In contrast, out-of-state processors were required to submit title certificates or police certificates.
sentences.chinese: 可是州外的收集者却要提交特许证或警察发给的证书。

sentences.english: Proofs submitted by the printer should be carefully checked to eliminate typographical errors.
sentences.chinese: 排版工人应当仔细核对提交的校样，避免印刷错误。

definition: to present/to give/to hand over/to hand in/to lay before
to fill in a form/to write data in a box (on a questionnaire or web form)
to report to one's superiors/to appear in the news/to reply to a letter
to report (to the authorities)/to declare (to customs)
proposal/draft resolution/motion (to be debated)/to propose a bill/to make a proposal
